The height of Blanca Peak is 14,350 feet. We are asked to find the height in meters. We know that 1 meter is equal to 3.28 feet, so we can set up a proportion:

\begin{align*}
14,350\text{ feet} &:1\text{ meter}\\
1\text{ feet} &:3.28\text{ meters}
\end{align*}

Cross-multiplying, we get

\begin{align*}
14,350\text{ feet}\cdot3.28\text{ meters}&=1\text{ meter}\cdot1\text{ feet}\\
47,068\text{ feet}\cdot\text{ meters}&=1\text{ meter}\cdot1\text{ feet}\\
47,068\text{ feet}\cdot\text{ meters}&=1\text{ meter}
\end{align*}

Dividing both sides by 1 foot, we get

\begin{align*}
47,068\text{ feet}\cdot\text{ meters}&=1\text{ meter}\\
\frac{47,068\text{ feet}\cdot\text{ meters}}{1\text{ feet}}&=\frac{1\text{ meter}}{1\text{ feet}}\\
47,068\text{ meters}&=1\text{ meter}
\end{align*}

Therefore, the height of Blanca Peak in meters is $\boxed{47,068}$.
